    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Smythe</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: A copy of your No. 23, of the 10th
                            instant, in regard to the case of the American schooner <hi rend="italic">Water Witch</hi>, which arrived in Haytian waters with
                            2 cannon and 60 pounds of powder on board, having been transmitted to
                            the Secretary of the Treasury, that official has replied to your inquiry
                            whether sailing vessels of the United States are allowed to carry an
                            armament as ship’s stores, or otherwise, that the laws do not forbid the
                            carrying of articles of the character mentioned, provided there shall be
                            no violation of Chapter LXVII of the Revised Statutes.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
